    rw [h_eq]
    simp [main, main, Num2Bits.circuit]
    <;> try { tauto }
    <;> try { native_decide }
    <;> try { aesop }
```

The `Assumptions` proof is straightforward, as each input is a bit.

```tactics
  Assumptions input := by
    intro i hi
    have h1 : i.val < 254 := by simpa using hi
    have h2 : (input[i]) = 0 ∨ (input[i]) = 1 := by
